entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: why

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am kinda quiet but i also like i probably would say borderline i like outside activities but i mainly kinda do activities probably by myself so yeah i would say i am an introvert slightly

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay what are some things that make you really mad

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: wow just maybe a racist or disrespectful person

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what do you do when you are annoyed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i kinda shut down and and reevaluate how i am as a person how i am coming off to other people i can not change anyone else is personality but i can work on my own

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: h how are you at controlling your temper

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am pretty good

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good when was the last time you argued with someone and what was it about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i usually do not argue with people i usually walk away i mean a argent does not settle anything

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i am sorry to hear that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: thank you

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how close are you to them

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i was extremely close to my mother that was who i am as a person who made me as a person

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what advice would you give yourself ten or twenty years ago

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: wow twenty ten years ago i would tell myself not to be so angry so upset all the time about things i can not control i would tell myself to relax and not be so hard on myself

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay what do you think of today is kids

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i think that is pretty cool i think you should have different avenues to deal with different people

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay have you ever served in the military

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no i have not

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no i have not

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how long ago were you diagnosed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: less than a month

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what got you to seek help

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i realized i have to evaluate myself as a person so i can not really look to anyone else to help me unless i i start with myself

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you still go to therapy now

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no i do not

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: why did you stop

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i feel like as a person as a individual i feel like i should be able to control things myself i feel like to go seek out help is good for someone else it probably is very good for other people i have worked with that population of ptsd veterans before so i know that it helps a lot of people but i do not feel like it is for me

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how hard is that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it is not difficult at all i have always been like a loner someone who who tries to handle to handle my own problems and situations

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i see how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: a little depressed but i think everyone is it has a little bit of sadness in them at some point

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how do you cope with them

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: day by day day by day i just started a exercise program so i am trying to look at myself for the solution

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is great did you think you had a problem before you found out

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: always known ever since i was a child things moved me differently than other kids so i felt like i was always different i felt like if i was gonna ever understand me as a person then i would have to work on myself so yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay when was the last time you felt really happy

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: today i got to see my best friend after a long time so i mean happiness comes and goes but i felt happy today

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is great how would your best friend describe you

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: wow he would say really silly but still when i am around him i try to be happy i try to present a a a situation where we are both gonna be happy no one wants to be around a depressed person

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how do you know them

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: scrubbedentry

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: cool what would you say are some of your best qualities

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: wow i mean on certain days everything could be my best quality but i would say i am loyal i am dependable i would just say i try to be there in the moment i am not a person who who is really fat flashy excuse me flashy or into materialistic things so i feel like i am very grounded

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: h who is someone that is been a positive influence in your life

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: oh my mother by far my sisters

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: can you tell me about that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: my mom was a school teacher which made me wanna become a school teacher and that is basically what i have been doing my sister has been at her job for forty years so i have always had a stable influence in my life
